@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "What is a Database?";
}

<div class="container">
    <h1>What is a Database?</h1>
    <p>A <strong>database</strong> is like a digital storage cabinet where we keep information in an organized way.</p>

    <p>Imagine you're trying to remember the names of all your classmates. If you write them down on random sticky notes, you might lose track. But if you write them in a notebook with names under a "Name" column and birthdays under a "Birthday" column — now that's a simple database!</p>

    <p>So, a database helps us <strong>store</strong>, <strong>organize</strong>, and <strong>retrieve</strong> data easily.</p>

    <div class="navigation-buttons">
        <a href="@Url.Action("WhyDatabase", "Database")" class="btn btn-primary">Next &raquo;</a>
    </div>
</div>

